  "doc_id": "14458",
  "text": "Xu et al. cultivated B. braunii in both 2 L and 40 L airlift bioreactors. The aim of the research was to optimize the inner structure of a cylindrical airlift bioreactor using a two-dimensional axisymmetric CFD model. This was achieved by designing an effective mixing process to improve the growth rate and increase the hydrocarbon content (up to 75% of its dry biomass). The result showed that CFD simulation were validated with experimental data collected from microalgae cultures in 2 L and 40 L airlift bioreactors. Hence allowed the optimization of the inner structure of bioreactor suitable for microalgae cultivation without required numerous time-consuming bioreactor experiments [CITATION_1] .",
